<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 31 at 4:44AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Reduced Visibility this Morning...
Patchy fog has developed across the Helena Valley this morning
and is expected to persist through the 8 AM to 10 AM MST hours
before gradually dissipating. While most locations will see
reductions in visibility to between 1 to 3 miles, northern
portions of the valley near Lake Helena may see localized
reduction to near half of a mile.
Travelers should be prepared for reduced visibility. Slow down,
allow extra time to reach your destination, and use low beam
headlights.</description>
